The paper deals with algorithm design for a combinatorial optimization problem, which suggests that it belongs to the category of theoretical computer science (cs). The problem is related to partitioning, which is a common topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the structural properties of the problem, which is a characteristic of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem is NP-hard, which implies that it is related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
